INSERT INTO `gossip_menu` (`entry`,`text_id`) VALUES (10211,14182); -- In the table gossip_menu, you list the gossipID and text_id that you want displayed. The gossipID for a type 2 GO is data3. The conditions in this table are the same ones that are used for loot. So if you look on the wiki under loot, you will see what values you can use. In this case I used condition 9 (CONDITION_QUESTTAKEN) with quest ID 12828. What this means is that if you have ACCEPTED quest 12828, then you should see this gossip from the GO with gossipID 10211. Follow me so far?
INSERT INTO `gossip_menu_option` (`menu_id`,`id`,`option_id`,`action_script_id`) VALUES (10211,1,1,@script); -- Here we have a similar case to gossip_menu. The conditions are the same as the ones used for loot. The way this works is, if you have a gossip_menu, you can do additional things with a gossip_menu_option that has the same menu_id as the entry in gossip_menu. So, here we have 10211 and then the id is an arbitrary field for the order you want them to occur / appear in. Since only 1 I picked 1. action_script_id is the ID of the script you want to execute from gossip_scripts. Again, condition 9 is CONDITION_QUESTTAKEN and quest is 12828.
